Bromon Aircraft Co, which is privatelyheld, said it is in the final design phase of a twin turboprop,and is scheduled to complete production of three prototypeaircraft in the fall of 1988.    It also said it expects certification by the FederalAviation Administration in 1988.    The turboprop, the BR-2000, can carry up to 46 passengersor up to six tons of cargo, according to the company. Reuter&#3;